mes such as   Ermintrude   containing the word <i>erm(en)</i>, <i>irm(en)</i> ‘entire’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, but its popularity in medieval England was greatly enhanced by the fact that it had been borne by the mother of Edward the Confessor, herself a Norman. In modern times, it was only in moderate use early in the 20th century but rose sharply in favour in the 1970s and has since remained perennially popular."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705185,"age":4,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705187,"age":113,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Baroness Emma Fitzrobert was born in 1102, in Marston Moretaine, Bedfordshire, England. She had at least 5 sons with Robert de Morteyn."},"et":{"1102–":"1102–Surnud","1096–1175":"1096–1175","1128–Male":"1128–Surnud","1130–1180":"1130–1180","1130–Male":"1130–Surnud","1132–Male":"8.jaanuar1132kuni7.jaanuar1133–Surnud","1134–Male":"1134–Surnud","1102–Female":"1102–Surnud","ABT. 1130":"umbes 1130","1128":"1128","1106":"1106","1215":"1215","ABT. 1134":"umbes 1134","1102":"1102","1134":"1134","1132":"8. jaanuar 1132 kuni 7. jaanuar 1133","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1096":"1096","1180":"1180","Nottinghamshire, England":"Notti